# Touch Sensor Module Reverse Engineering

## Overview

This repository contains the reverse engineering of a **Touch Sensor Module (TTP223)**. The objective of this project is to understand the module's hardware design by analyzing the PCB, identifying the components, and recreating the schematic in KiCad.

## Objectives

* Analyze the Touch Sensor Module PCB.
* Identify the major electronic components.
* Recreate the schematic in KiCad.
* Understand the working principle of capacitive touch sensing.
* Improve PCB analysis and hardware reverse engineering skills.

## What I Learned

* Capacitive touch sensing fundamentals.
* TTP223 touch sensor IC pin connections.
* PCB trace analysis.
* Schematic capture using KiCad.
* Component identification and verification.

## Tools Used

* KiCad
* Digital Multimeter (for continuity testing, if required)
* Datasheet
* Magnifier/PCB inspection

